snippet.title: Marvel Studios' Wonder Man - Official Teaser Trailer (2026) Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, Ben Kingsley
snippet.description:
Take a look at the 'Casting' Teaser Trailer for Wonder Man, the next action-adventure superhero installment in the MCU distributed by Marvel Studios. Wonder Man is streaming in January 2026 exclusively on Disney+.

Hollywood actor Simon Williams is thrust into the world of superheroes as he gets powers of his own, and becomes the new superhero Wonder Man.

Wonder Man stars Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, Ben Kingsley, Demetrius Grosse, Lauren Glazier, Byron Bowers, and more. The series was created by Destin Daniel Cretton.

Wonder Man is streaming in January 2026 exclusively on Disney+.

#WonderMan #MCU #IGN

Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

⚖️ The Equalizer 4

Rumors suggest Robert McCall may be pulled from hard-won quiet when a transnational protection racket targets the few people he still trusts. Chatter imagines Keanu Reeves and Jason Statham entering as lethal wild cards—potential rivals, uneasy allies, or both—forcing McCall to navigate a dead-drop maze where every favor has a price and every room is a trap.

Speculation points to grounded, surgical set pieces: tight apartments with improvised tools, rain-slick night streets, and daylight ambushes that hinge on timing rather than spectacle. Fans picture a tone of moral chess—measured dialogue, sudden violence, and tradecraft that values patience over bravado—while the score simmers under ticking percussion.

Nothing is official, but whispers envision a finale that reframes what “equalizing” means: three professionals colliding over justice, debt, and who gets to protect whom, leaving the door open for future cross-paths if the stars align.

God can’t save us!
(We’re laughing either way)
God can’t save us!”
1, 2, 1, 2, 3 come on

snippet.title: Season 19: Haunted Masquerade Official Trailer | Overwatch 2
snippet.description:
Masks, Mythics, and mayhem await in Season 19: Haunted Masquerade!

Join us for this year’s spooktacular Halloween event, Haunted Masquerade! Grab a mask of a fellow teammate and discover new ways to synergize when you use powerful new ability combos.

Sojourn, Torbjörn, and Hazard are stepping into the Stadium arena this season with exciting new Powers and Items you won’t want to miss. Gadgets are also making their Stadium debut in the Armory, giving you even more ways to power up your Hero and dominate the competition.

Go green or go home with Lifeweaver’s new Divine Druid Mythic Hero Skin which you can unlock by using the 80 Mythic Prisms you earn through the Season 19 Ultimate Battle Pass.

And that’s just the beginning! Be on the look out for brand new Shop Bundles, a returning fan-favorite collaboration, and SO much more! See our Season 19 Dev Update for more details: https://youtu.be/ktRThtjqCE8

Season 19: Haunted Masquerade creeps in on Oct 14!
